==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reinforced concrete
<hw>Re`in*forced con"crete</hw>. <def>Concrete having within its mass a
system of iron or steel supports, such as bars, rods, or a heavy mesh,
to provide increased tensile strength and shear resistance. Same as
<er>Ferro-concrete</er>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>reenforced
concrete</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reinforcement</ent>⟦br⟧
